    <section id="tips" class="card">
        <h2>Watering & care tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Water early morning to reduce evaporation.</li>
            <li>Feed with compost tea every 2–3 weeks during peak growth.</li>
            <li>Use mulch to keep roots cool and soil moist.</li>
            <li>Rotate crops: avoid planting tomatoes in the same spot two years in a row.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            If pests appear, start with the least invasive method (hand picking, water spray)
            before moving to stronger measures. Wearing gloves (<kbd>G</kbd>) is optional but recommended.
        </p>
    </section>

