    <section id="faq" class="card">
        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <details>
            <summary>How often should I water?</summary>
            <p>Most container plants need checking daily in hot weather. Water when the top 2–3 cm are dry.</p>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>What fertilizer should I use?</summary>
            <p>Look for balanced organic options. For leafy greens, higher nitrogen (N) helps. For roots, more phosphorus (P).</p>
        </details>

        <details>
            <summary>Do I need special soil for containers?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Use a light potting mix—garden soil compacts and reduces root oxygen.</p>
        </details>
