    <article class="card">
        <h2>Case study: Balcony herb success</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Goal:</strong> Fresh herbs all year in a 1 m² space. <strong>Constraints:</strong> Partial shade,
            wind exposure, and limited watering time.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Approach:</strong> We chose basil, parsley, mint, and chives in 30 cm deep planters. A simple
            drip system (timer + hose) watered plants every morning for 10 minutes. We mulched with shredded leaves.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>Results:</strong> Continuous harvest of 2–3 handfuls per week. The mint needed containment; basil
            thrived with weekly tip pinching. Overall, a flavorful victory!
        </p>
